  • Method Details

    • executeInternalMethod

      public static boolean executeInternalMethod(String fqn, String method) throws ReflectiveOperationException

      This method helps HappyTree API to cover code blocks that is not accessible from outside for JUnit tests purposes.

      The test must provide the fully qualified name of the class and the method name to be tested. This only works for methods with no parameters.

      Parameters:
      fqn - fully qualified name of the class
      method - representing the method name
      Returns:
      the boolean result of the method execution
      Throws:
      ReflectiveOperationException - if any reflection error occurs
